SIMPLE: floccule
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Floccule
<hw>Floc"cule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Flocculus</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A detached mass of loosely
fibrous structure like a shredded tuft of wool.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Specif.: A small particle of an
insoluble substance formed in a liquid by the union of smaller
particles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flocculence</ent>⟦br⟧
